thread.title: JOSE
thread.title_full: Redspot Car Rentals reviewed by JOSE

author: JOSE
title: JOSE
text: When we arrived at Sydney, there were not many vehicles available from any rental agencies so we had to take what was available. The car was very small and cramped because it was a 2-door, which I would have never expected in a rental. Maps are not available at all because GPS is offered. If you don't get the GPS option, then you are on your own. The intake person when we returned the car was very pleasant and helpful in guiding us to where we needed to be for our departure. I wish I could remember her name.
